==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*xraigran-'', whence also Old Saxon ''higara'' (Dutch ''[[reiger]]''), Old High German ''[[heigaro]]'' and ''[[reigaro]]'' (German ''[[Reiher]]''), Old Norse ''[[hegri]]'' (Swedish ''[[häger]]''). Compare also French ''[[héron]]''
